Palu is the capital of the central Sulawesi province, located a narrow bay on the west coast of Sulawesi Island, with an estimated population of 379 800 in 2017.
The earthquake and tsunami hit the city in the middle of its 40th anniversary.
The municipality of Donggala extends over 300 kilometres (180 miles) to Sulawesi Island on the north-west coast line.
