The main economic activities of the Central Sulawesi Province, and in particular the coastal region of Donggala, are fishing and agriculture.
Nickel mining is also important, but it is concentrated in Morowal on the opposite coast of Sulawesi.
According to the Indonesian Disaster Mitigation Agency, several tsunamis have struck the country in the last 100 years.
